{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban on requiring an app to access purchased tickets",
        "additional_details": "Many providers sell physical paper tickets as a matter of customer preference, and to include people with limited access or skills with digital devices.\r\n\r\nWe are concerned that some platforms mandate the use of a specific, proprietary mobile app, which may only be available on selected devices, gravely limiting customer choice.\r\n",
        "background": "The government should update relevant legislation, so digital tickets can always be accessed offline without a mobile app.\r\n \r\nWe think possible arguments regarding security do not outweigh the necessity of customer choice, access, and control",
